en-us: This includes High-risk critical workers* in the following industries: agriculture, fishing vessel crews, food processing, grocery store/food bank, corrections (prisons, jails, detention centers), court of law, public transit, and remaining first responders, educators and school staff for pre-kindergarten through 12th grade, and child care workers
es-us: Esto incluye trabajadores críticos de alto riesgo* en las siguientes industrias: agricultura, equipos de barcos pesqueros, procesamiento de alimentos, tienda de comestibles/banco de alimentos, correcciones (prisiones, cárceles, centros de detención), tribunal de justicia, transporte público y socorristas restantes, educadores y personal escolar para preescolar hasta 12º grado, y trabajadores de cuidado infantil

en-us:
This includes high-risk critical workers in the following industries: 
- agriculture
- fishing vessel crews
- food processing
- grocery store/food bank
- corrections (prisons, jails, detention centers)
- courts of law
- public transit
- remaining first responders
- educators and school staff for pre-kindergarten through 12th grade and child care workers
- those who work in an enclosed space around other people and cannot maintain physical distance.
es-us:
Esto incluye trabajadores críticos de alto riesgo en las siguientes industrias: 
- agricultura
- tripulaciones de buques pesqueros
- elaboración de alimentos
- tienda de comestibles/banco de alimentos
- correcciones (prisiones, cárceles, centros de detención)
- tribunales de justicia
- transporte público
- restantes socorristas
- educadores y personal escolar para trabajadores de preescolar hasta 12º grado y cuidado infantil
- aquellos que trabajan en un espacio cerrado alrededor de otras personas y no pueden mantener la distancia física.

en-us:
People with disabilities wondering about their eligibility should apply the definition to their situation: Does their disability put them at increased risk for COVID-19? They can also work with their health care provider to assess their eligibility. In particular, Down syndrome increases risk for severe illness and is on the CDC list. Research continues to emerge on other developmental and intellectual disabilities that put someone at increased risk, so these eligibility guidelines lean toward inclusiveness.

People with disabilities are eligible in 1B tier 2 if:

Their disability alone puts them at higher risk for severe illness from COVID-19 (e.g. Down syndrome).
They have a disability that doesn't alone put them at higher risk but they also have another underlying condition from the CDC list. (e.g. A person who is deaf and has Type 2 diabetes).
es-us:
Las personas con discapacidades que se preguntan acerca de su elegibilidad deben aplicar la definición a su situación: ¿Su discapacidad los pone en mayor riesgo de COVID-19? También pueden trabajar con su proveedor de atención médica para evaluar su elegibilidad. En particular, el síndrome de Down aumenta el riesgo de enfermedad grave y está en la lista de los CDC. Continúan surgiendo investigaciones sobre otras discapacidades intelectuales e intelectuales del desarrollo que ponen a alguien en mayor riesgo, por lo que estas pautas de elegibilidad se inclinan hacia la inclusión.

Las personas con discapacidades son elegibles en 1B nivel 2 si:

Su discapacidad por sí sola los pone en mayor riesgo de enfermedad grave de COVID-19 (por ejemplo, síndrome de Down).
Tienen una discapacidad que no solo los pone en mayor riesgo, pero también tienen otra condición subyacente de la lista de los CDC. (por ejemplo, una persona sorda y con diabetes tipo 2).

en-us: VA Puget Sound is now providing Pfizer, Moderna, and Johnson & Johnson's Janssen vaccines depending on the site, which include:  Seattle, American Lake, Silverdale, Mount Vernon, and our Mobile Medical Unit. We continue to proactively contact Veterans to make vaccine appointments. Please, no walk-in vaccines, they are by appointment only. Eligible Veterans can also call us directly at 206-716-5716 to schedule, or contact their primary care team.
es-us: VA Puget Sound ahora está proporcionando vacunas Janssen de Pfizer, Moderna y Johnson &s dependiendo del sitio, que incluyen: Seattle, American Lake, Silverdale, Mount Vernon y nuestra Unidad Médica Móvil. Seguimos contactando proactivamente a veteranos para hacer citas con vacunas. Por favor, no hay vacunas para caminar, son sólo con cita previa. Los Veteranos Elegibles también pueden llamarnos directamente al 206-716-5716 para programar, o comunicarse con su equipo de atención primaria.

People with disabilities wondering about their eligibility should apply the definition to their situation: Does their disability put them at increased risk for COVID-19? They can also work with their health care provider to assess their eligibility. In particular, Down syndrome increases risk for severe illness and is on the CDC list. Research continues to emerge on other developmental and intellectual disabilities that put someone at increased risk, so these eligibility guidelines lean toward inclusiveness.

People with disabilities are eligible in 1B tier 2 if:

Their disability alone puts them at higher risk for severe illness from COVID-19 (e.g. Down syndrome).
They have a disability that doesn't alone put them at higher risk but they also have another underlying condition from the CDC list. (e.g. A person who is deaf and has Type 2 diabetes).

This includes people, staff, and volunteers in certain congregate living settings: correctional facilities; group homes for people with disabilities; settings where people experiencing homelessness live or access services

This includes those who have two or more of the following:
- Cancer
- Chronic kidney disease
- Chronic lung diseases, including COPD (chronic obstructive pulmonary disease), asthma (moderate-to-severe), interstitial lung disease, cystic fibrosis, and pulmonary hypertension
- Dementia or other neurological conditions
- Diabetes (type 1 or type 2)
- Down syndrome
- Heart conditions (such as heart failure, coronary artery disease, cardiomyopathies or hypertension)
- HIV infection
- Immunocompromised state (weakened immune system)
- Liver disease
- Overweight and obesity
- Pregnancy
- Sickle cell disease or thalassemia
- Smoking, current or former
- Solid organ or blood stem cell transplant
- Stroke or cerebrovascular disease, which affects blood flow to the brain
- Substance use disorders
